# Vendo as variaveis

# age in days
# gender 1 - women, 2 - men
# height cm
# weight kg
# ap_hi Systolic blood pressure
# ap_lo Diastolic blood pressure
# cholesterol 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# gluc 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# smoke whether patient smokes or not
# alco Binary feature
# active Binary feature
# cardio Target variable

Ajuste de parâmetros

levels(cardio_train_fil$cardio) <- c("No", "Yes")

# Escolher o melhor k 

set.seed(123)
ctrl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", 
                     number = 10,
                     repeats = 3,
                     classProbs = TRUE,
                           ## Evaluate performance using 
                           ## the following function
                           summaryFunction = twoClassSummary)
tuneGrid <- expand.grid(k = 1:50)           
knnFit <- train(cardio ~ .,
      method     = "knn",
      preProcess = c("center","scale"),
      # method = "center" subtracts the mean of the predictor's data 
      # (again from the data in x) from the predictor values 
      # while method = "scale" divides by the standard deviation
      tuneLength = 20,
      trControl  = ctrl,
      tuneGrid = tuneGrid,
      metric = "ROC",
      data       = cardio_train_fil)
knnFit

# Lendo os dados

filmes <- read.csv("filmes.csv", header = T, sep = ";")
filmes
# Organizando os dados
filmes$Movie.ID <- NULL
row.names(filmes) <- filmes$Movie.Name
filmes$Movie.Name <- NULL

library(FastKNN)

# Novo exemplo
example <- as.data.frame(t(c(7.2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0)))
colnames(example) <- colnames(filmes)

# Distancia
dist <- as.data.frame(Distance_for_KNN_test(example, filmes))
colnames(dist) <- row.names(filmes)
